        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-03-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="565" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                <head>No. 565.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L. S.
                                    Sackville West</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-03-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 22, 1888</date>
                                (Received March 23.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note of the 19th
                            instant, suggesting that each Government should beat liberty to publish
                            the joint protocols of the Samoan conference, I have the honor to inform
                            you that Her Majesty’s Government are of opinion that, pending the
                            re-assembling of the conference, its proceedings should be considered
                            confidential, and that the publication of them at present might
                            prejudice the satisfactory solution of the question.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">L. S.
                                    Sackville-West.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
